========================================
DISPATCHARR v0.26.0 UUID LOGGING FIX
========================================
Fixes: "Could not log channel start event" when channel_id is a stream_hash (SHA256)
       instead of a valid UUID (e.g. stream preview mode).

Affects: apps/proxy/live_proxy/server.py - initialize_channel() method

Apply with: patch -p0 < dispatcharr_v0.26.0_uuid_logging_fix.patch
Or manually apply changes to the file listed below.

========================================
FIX: UUID Validation Before DB Query
========================================

--- a/apps/proxy/live_proxy/server.py
+++ b/apps/proxy/live_proxy/server.py
@@ -738,9 +738,16 @@
 
             # Log channel start event
             try:
-                _name = Channel.objects.filter(uuid=channel_id).values_list('name', flat=True).first()
-                channel_name = _name if _name else str(channel_id)
+                channel_name = str(channel_id)
+                # Safely try to get the channel name - channel_id may not be a valid UUID (e.g. stream preview uses stream_hash)
+                try:
+                    import uuid as uuid_module
+                    uuid_module.UUID(str(channel_id))
+                    _name = Channel.objects.filter(uuid=channel_id).values_list('name', flat=True).first()
+                    if _name:
+                        channel_name = _name
+                except (ValueError, AttributeError):
+                    # channel_id is not a UUID (e.g. stream hash) - use string representation
+                    pass
+
                 self._channel_names[channel_id] = channel_name
 
                 # Get stream name if stream_id is available